      {
        "id" : "17f1ea5d-151f-4623-a350-ddff42cafcb3",
        "parentId" : "0c34cc2c-1969-4cea-930c-d730c503ea77",
        "authorId" : "92fc8a78-5aad-454c-9b1f-3b0641161b09",
        "body" : "I thought we would have one feedstock for the library itself, and one for every binding. Did I got that wrong? There is something I must missing.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-06-09T14:41:04Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-06-09T14:41:04Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "92fc8a78-5aad-454c-9b1f-3b0641161b09",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "103f9ede-82f4-4d9e-b4ab-538c4a94e501",
        "parentId" : "0c34cc2c-1969-4cea-930c-d730c503ea77",
        "authorId" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "body" : "You did not get it wrong. I am actually trying to open a discussion on how to proceed. I am OK having different recipes for each binding, but ideally we should have 1 recipe that could produce all the packages (like RPMs), do avoid the maintenance overhead.\n\nHaving multiple recipes is an extra burden on the maintainers that we should take into account. (Again, I am not leaning to any side, just rambling...)\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-06-09T14:45:33Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-06-09T14:45:33Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "6d679ec7-fcaf-474a-8739-7fd8e8a6c8d1",
        "parentId" : "0c34cc2c-1969-4cea-930c-d730c503ea77",
        "authorId" : "92fc8a78-5aad-454c-9b1f-3b0641161b09",
        "body" : "Got the point. This surely will make things easier for maintainers. This would work for `eccodes` because of the bundling. Would it also be possible for netcdf-c, -fortran, -cxx, and the python nectdf4?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-06-09T14:54:43Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-06-09T14:54:43Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "92fc8a78-5aad-454c-9b1f-3b0641161b09",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "b15c2add-ec70-49b4-af94-c2de7fd1cfdf",
        "parentId" : "0c34cc2c-1969-4cea-930c-d730c503ea77",
        "authorId" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "body" : "> This would work for `eccodes` because of the bundling. Would it also be possible for netcdf-c, -fortran, -cxx, and the python nectdf4?\n\nThat is a good question that deserves its own issue :smile: \n\nIn the old days netCDF was bundled but now the source is all split. I think I saw an effort to build them all from `netcdf-c`, but I never tried. `netcdf4-python` is another story, but we could create a meta package if users think it is necessary.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-06-09T14:58:16Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-06-09T14:58:16Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "tags" : [
        ]
